sentences: Kavichandran Alexander (born May 3, 1949) is an audio engineer and record producer.
Alexander was the producer and engineer for the 1993 album A Meeting by the River, featuring Ry Cooder and Vishwa Mohan Bhatt, which won a Grammy Award for Best World Music Album.
In 1968, he moved to Paris, and at the age of 18, played in the French production of Hair by Shakespeare & Co.
In 1984, Alexander started the Water Lily Acoustics record label based in Santa Barbara, California.
